HEADWORD: Illaudable
<hw>Il*laud"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>illaudabilis</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Laudable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not laudable; not praise-worthy; worthy
of censure or disapprobation.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Il*laud"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Broome.</au></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ill-boding</ent>⟦br⟧
